# Voice-to-spec assistant (issue #43) — server-side only, never commit real values.
# Revised 2026-07-05: output is voice-in/text-out. No TTS, no ElevenLabs —
# that integration (api/tts.js, ELEVENLABS_API_KEY) has been removed.

# Get a key at https://console.groq.com — used by api/next-turn.js (picks
# the assistant's next question) and api/file-feedback.js (extracts the
# scope of work at session end).
GROQ_API_KEY=

# CLASSIC GitHub PAT (github.com/settings/tokens, NOT the fine-grained
# type at github.com/settings/personal-access-tokens) with `repo` +
# `project` scopes. Used by api/file-feedback.js to file the extracted
# scope of work as a Pending ticket AND add it to the VCP Tracker board.
# MUST be classic: fine-grained PATs cannot access Projects v2 boards
# owned by a personal user account at all (confirmed against GitHub's docs
# and live testing 2026-07-05 — only organization-owned boards have a
# fine-grained "Projects" permission; the VCP Tracker is owned by
# Joeareval19, a user, not an org). `repo` covers Issues + Contents;
# `project` is what actually reaches the board. Deliberately separate from
# BOARD_WEBHOOK_GITHUB_TOKEN (agent-dispatch pipeline, issue #51) — a
# compromise of one shouldn't extend to the other.
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# Supabase SERVICE ROLE key (not the anon/publishable key) for the vcp-ops
# project (qaorlbgrkpldcatyntlw) — used by BOTH api/next-turn.js (upserts
# the growing transcript to vcp_voice_sessions after every turn — see
# issue #43's durability requirement) and api/file-feedback.js (final
# upsert with summary/status, then updates filed_issue after a ticket is
# filed). The anon key cannot be used for either: vcp_voice_sessions' RLS
# policy is INSERT-only for anon (no select/update/delete), and an upsert
# needs to read/match an existing row by session_id. Get this from the
# Supabase dashboard's Project Settings -> API -> service_role key — treat
# it as a full-access database credential, never expose it client-side.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
